window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><i>The Story of Dr. Seuss</i> explores the fascinating life behind one of our favorite authors through rhyme. We know and love his books, including <i>The Cat in The Hat</i>, <i>The Grinch</i>, and <i>Green Eggs and Ham</i>, and now we can get to really know the man himself.</p> <p>In this short and fun biography, you will learn about Ted’s early years, family life, path to success, building and flourishing in his writing career and beyond!</p> <p>About the author: Amba Brown is an Australian author, living in New York City who has written multiple non-fiction books published by various houses including <i>HarperCollins Publishers</i> and <i>John Catt Educational Publishing</i>. She is also the creator of The Finding Your Path Book Series. Amba has been featured internationally, sharing her message with the <i>Huffington Post</i>, <i>Reader’s Diges</i>t, and at <i>TEDx</i>.</p>"; 
